{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"usefulItems":"springform cake tin (20 cm), baking paper, wire rack, wooden skewer, oven","id":"r119119","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-9TRiu1d7vFs\/XZWd-NN2qzI\/AAAAAAAAes0\/Vzxb35Mhs20gm-TXhplPxRowHgn1CEplgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_PgtO7mBsjS2qc_HA.png","title":"Apple, pear and bay leaf cake","publishedAt":"2017-01-22T00:00:00Z","ingredients":[{"content":"150 g unsalted butter, cut into pieces (2 cm), plus extra for greasing"},{"content":"160 g buckwheat"},{"content":"100 g raw almonds"},{"content":"120 g Rapadura sugar"},{"content":"1 dried bay leaf"},{"content":"1 pear (approx. 100 g), peeled and cored"},{"content":"1 tsp vanilla bean paste"},{"content":"3 eggs"},{"content":"2 tsp baking powder"},{"content":"1 pinch salt"},{"content":"1 Granny Smith apple, peeled, cored and cut into thin slices (5 mm)"},{"content":"brown sugar, for sprinkling"},{"content":"whipped cream, to serve (see Tips) (optional)"}],"nutrition":{"protein":"6.6 g","fat":"24.6 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"28.9 g","calories":"1525 kJ \/ 363 kcal"},"preparations":[{"content":"Preheat oven to 170°C. Grease and line a springform cake tin (20 cm) with baking paper and set aside."},{"content":"Place buckwheat, almonds, sugar and bay leaf into mixing bowl and mill <b>12 sec\/speed 9<b>."},{"content":"Add butter, pear, vanilla, eggs, baking powder and salt and mix <b>50 sec\/speed 5<b>."},{"content":"Pour mixture into prepared tin. Fan apple slices over cake in a circular pattern, then sprinkle with brown sugar."},{"content":"Bake for 55 minutes (170°C), or until cake springs back when touched and a wooden skewer inserted into the centre of the cake comes out clean. Transfer onto a wire rack to cool completely, then serve with whipped cream (optional)."}],"hintsAndTricks":["You can replace whipped cream with yoghurt.","This cake can be made with other seasonal fruits (e.g apricot, peach or plum).","You can use a fresh or dried bay leaf in this recipe or experiment with different flavours by replacing the bay leaf with rosemary (12 leaves) or sage (4 leaves).","You can replace the buckwheat with buckwheat flour, wholemeal flour or plain flour.","You can make this cake using a 22 cm cake tin - the cake will be a bit thinner, but the baking time will stay the same."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","1h 15m","10 portions"]}